article.story: NEW YORK -- — Japhet Medor's 16 points helped Fordham defeat Manhattan 93-61 on Monday night. Medor added six assists and three steals for the Rams (3-3). Elijah Gray added 15 points while shooting 7 for 11, including 0 for 3 from beyond the arc, and they also had seven rebounds. Kyle Rose shot 4 for 6 (3 for 4 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line to finish with 14 points, while adding seven rebounds and four steals. Daniel Rouzan finished with 15 points for the Jaspers (3-3). Briggs McClain added 10 points for Manhattan. Shaquil Bender also had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
